Additionally, a methyl group on the alpha carbon of the aldehyde increases the molecular weight and steric hindrance, which typically raises the melting point. The effect of a methyl group is seen in the comparison of ethanal (-123°C) to propanal (-81°C), giving an approximate increase of +42°C.
